5. SCORING ALGORITHM

Each question maps to exactly one of the 5 dimensions (6 questions per dimension).
Each response is scored 0–4 based on severity (first option = 0, last option = 4).
Dimension score = (sum of 6 responses / 24) × 100, expressed as a percentage.
Overall Anxiety Index = mean of all 5 dimension scores.
Severity classification: 0–30% = Mild, 31–60% = Moderate, 61–100% = Severe.
Profile Type assignment:

Primary type = the dimension with the highest score.
If two or more dimensions are within 10 percentage points of each other AND both are above 50%, assign "The Storm" (multi-dimensional) as primary type.
Secondary type = second-highest dimension, noted in the report if its score is above 40%.


Tie-breaking: If two dimensions are exactly tied (and not qualifying for "The Storm"), assign based on this priority order: Separation > Generalised > Social > Noise > Routine (based on clinical prevalence).


