7. TECH REQUIREMENTS

Mobile-first responsive design. Most traffic will come from social media on phones.
Fast page loads. Aim for <2 second load time on the landing page. Minimise JavaScript bundle size. Lazy-load non-critical assets.
Stripe integration for one-time payments and future subscription billing.
Email integration — automated sequences (see Section 6). Transactional email for report delivery.
PDF generation — server-side. Use quiz answers + scoring algorithm to populate a report template programmatically. The PDF must include charts (radar chart, bar charts) generated as images/SVGs and embedded. Use a library like Puppeteer, WeasyPrint, or React-pdf — whichever produces the most professional output.
Database — store: user data (email, name), pet data (name, breed, age, species), quiz responses (all 30 answers), scores (5 dimensions + overall), profile type assigned, payment status, timestamps. Use PostgreSQL or SQLite — whichever is simpler for deployment.
Admin dashboard (simple, password-protected page):

Total assessments completed (today / this week / all time)
Total reports purchased (today / this week / all time)
Conversion rate: free result → paid report
Revenue (today / this week / all time)
A/B test results: conversion rate at $9.90 vs $19.90
Email signup count
Top profile types distribution (pie chart)


SEO: meta title, meta description, Open Graph tags (with radar chart image for social sharing), JSON-LD schema markup (Quiz schema), sitemap.xml, robots.txt.
Analytics: Google Analytics 4 with event tracking on: assessment started, assessment completed, email submitted, report purchased, share button clicked. OR Plausible Analytics if simpler.
Legal pages: Privacy Policy page (GDPR + PDPA compliant), Terms of Service page, Cookie consent banner (opt-in, not assumed).
Social sharing: auto-generate an Open Graph image per result (profile type + pet name + radar chart) for rich social previews when the result link is shared.


